metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-wordspec_2.13/index.json:9:    "description": "ScalaTest WordSpec provides the WordSpec style for writing behavior-driven ScalaTest suites using nested words and sentences to describe a system under test. It includes synchronous, asynchronous, and fixture-based suite classes that integrate with ScalaTest assertions, matchers, tagging, and test lifecycle features.",
metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-refspec_2.13/index.json:9:    "description": "ScalaTest RefSpec provides the RefSpec testing style for ScalaTest on the JVM, where tests are represented by methods and discovered via reflection. It integrates with ScalaTest's core assertions, tagging, fixtures, and reporting so Scala projects can define and run method-oriented test suites.",
metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-mustmatchers_2.13/index.json:9:    "description" : "ScalaTest Must Matchers provides the must-style matcher syntax for ScalaTest assertions on the JVM. It supplies the org.scalatest.matchers.must.Matchers API, allowing tests to express expectations such as values must equal, include, contain, start with, or satisfy custom matchers.",
metadata/org.jline/jline-terminal-jni/index.json:9:    "description" : "JLine JNI Terminal provides the JLine terminal provider implementation that uses JLine's JNI native library for low-level terminal and pseudoterminal access. It plugs into the JLine terminal API to support native console operations across supported platforms without relying on JNA or external process execution.",
metadata/org.jline/jline-terminal-jni/index.json:44:    "description" : "JLine JNI Terminal provides the JLine terminal provider implementation that uses JLine's JNI native library for low-level terminal and pseudoterminal access. It plugs into the JLine terminal API to support native console operations across supported platforms without relying on JNA or external process execution.",
metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-shouldmatchers_2.13/index.json:9:    "description": "ScalaTest Should Matchers provides the should matcher syntax for expressing assertions in ScalaTest suites. It lets tests compare values, inspect collections and properties, and build readable expectations using ScalaTest's matcher DSL.",
metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-matchers-core_2.13/index.json:9:    "description": "ScalaTest Matchers Core provides the shared matcher result types, matcher abstractions, and DSL words used by ScalaTest's should and must matcher APIs. It lets Scala tests express type-safe assertions about equality, containment, ordering, patterns, properties, and custom matchers on the JVM.",
metadata/com.aayushatharva.brotli4j/brotli4j/index.json:9:    "description" : "Brotli4j provides Java bindings for Brotli compression and decompression using platform-specific native libraries. It exposes encoder and decoder APIs for working with Brotli-compressed data from JVM applications.",
metadata/org.jline/jline-terminal-jna/index.json:9:    "description" : "This module adds a JNA-backed terminal provider for JLine. It uses native platform APIs to manage terminals and pseudoterminals on supported operating systems.",
metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-featurespec_2.13/index.json:9:    "description": "ScalaTest FeatureSpec provides the FeatureSpec and AsyncFeatureSpec testing style for organizing ScalaTest suites around named features and scenarios. It supplies synchronous, asynchronous, and fixture-based specs for behavior-driven Scala tests while integrating with ScalaTest's assertions, matchers, reporting, and runner infrastructure.",
metadata/org.tpolecat/doobie-free_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "doobie-free_3 provides doobie's low-level free-algebra layer for representing JDBC operations as pure Scala 3 programs. It exposes direct mappings for JDBC objects such as connections, statements, result sets, and metadata so higher-level doobie modules and advanced users can interpret or compose database actions functionally.",
metadata/org.jboss.arquillian.junit/arquillian-junit-container/index.json:9:    "description" : "Arquillian JUnit Container integrates Arquillian's container test runtime with JUnit. It supplies the JUnit-side container extension and runner support needed to execute Arquillian tests against managed, remote, or embedded containers.",
metadata/com.aayushatharva.brotli4j/service/index.json:9:    "description" : "Brotli4j provides Brotli compression and decompression bindings for Java backed by native libraries. The service artifact contains the BrotliNativeProvider service interface used by Brotli4j native-provider JARs to advertise which platform-specific Brotli library they contain.",
metadata/com.google.guava/listenablefuture/index.json:10:    "description": "This artifact is an empty compatibility placeholder that Guava depends on so build tools prefer it over the standalone ListenableFuture artifact. It avoids duplicate ListenableFuture classes when applications depend on Guava and the older standalone coordinate at the same time.",
metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-compatible/index.json:9:    "description" : "scalatest-compatible provides the org.scalatest.compatible.Assertion marker interface used by ScalaTest-compatible assertion types. It lets third-party libraries define assertion results that can appear as the final expression in ScalaTest test bodies while avoiding Scala binary compatibility concerns.",
metadata/org.jboss.arquillian.junit/arquillian-junit-core/index.json:9:    "description" : "Arquillian JUnit Core provides the core JUnit integration for Arquillian, wiring JUnit test execution into Arquillian's test lifecycle. It supplies the Arquillian JUnit runner, ordering annotations, and extension hooks used by JUnit-based Arquillian tests.",
metadata/com.github.docker-java/docker-java-transport/index.json:9:    "description" : "docker-java-transport provides the core transport abstractions and shared utilities used by docker-java clients to communicate with the Docker Remote API. It defines common request and response plumbing that concrete transport implementations build on.",
metadata/org.tpolecat/typename_3/index.json:9:    "description" : "TypeName is a Scala micro-library that provides a typeName[A] method for producing a string representation of a Scala type and a TypeName[A] typeclass for requiring that a type has a name. It offers a lighter alternative to TypeTag-style machinery for diagnostics, error reporting, and similar code that needs readable type names.",
metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-funsuite_2.13/index.json:9:    "description" : "ScalaTest FunSuite provides the FunSuite testing style for ScalaTest on the JVM, where tests are registered as named functions rather than discovered as methods. It integrates with ScalaTest's assertions, fixtures, tagging, asynchronous suites, and reporting so Scala projects can write function-oriented unit tests.",
