metadata/org.scalatest/scalatest-freespec_2.13/index.json:9:    "description" : "ScalaTest FreeSpec provides ScalaTest's FreeSpec style, letting tests be written as nested, descriptive phrases that define a tree of behavior-focused examples. The artifact supplies the synchronous, asynchronous, fixture, and path-oriented FreeSpec classes for Scala 2.13 test suites.",
metadata/biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.bnd.annotation/index.json:9:    "description" : "The biz.aQute.bnd.annotation artifact provides bnd-specific Java annotations for OSGi bundle metadata, package versioning, capabilities, service metadata, JPMS hints, licenses, and plugin declarations. These annotations are consumed by bnd and related tooling to generate or validate bundle headers and metadata without hard-coding that information in build instructions.",
metadata/com.typesafe.netty/netty-reactive-streams/index.json:9:    "description" : "Netty Reactive Streams provides Reactive Streams Publisher and Subscriber channel handlers for Netty pipelines. It bridges Netty inbound and outbound messages with backpressure-aware reactive streams so applications can stream data through channels safely.",
metadata/commons-logging/commons-logging-api/index.json:9:    "description" : "Commons Logging API provides the public interfaces and factory classes used by Java code to log through an implementation-neutral abstraction. It lets libraries avoid depending directly on Log4J, JDK logging, LogKit, or another backend while allowing the application to choose the actual logging system at runtime.",
